snippet.title: Music Box TURNS ON by itself | Enter: The Old Gila County Jail
snippet.description:
We return to the Old Gila County jail with a special guest investigator: my mom. Watch our last investigation here: https://youtu.be/DE7o1XGKu1Q

Globe was established officially as a city in 1876 after many unsuccessful attempts to mine the area: mainly due to being driven off by the Apache Indians. 
Historians would not consider Globe modernized, comparatively to the wild west era, until after World War 1.
The Gila County Jail was built in 1910, two years before Arizona became a state, and remained operational until the 1980s.
In 1911, Kingsley Olds found himself in a jail cell after being accused of drowning two girls, LuLu and Mrytle Goswick, who were 10 and 12 years old. 
It's believed Wesley Goswick served his own dose of justice in the form of a bullet delivered into Kinglsey's cell. 
Whoever murdered Kingsley did so by taking keys from the janitor to the courthouse next door. They then fired a single shot through two sets of bars, hit Olds in the shoulder where the bullet entered his lungs, and left the rifle at the scene.


We experienced many unexplained instances that could be considered paranormal activity. Something was definitely trying to get our attention.
